<div id="node-3364" class="node node-type-story node-promoted node-teaser build-mode-teaser"><div class="node-inner">

  
      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/node/3364" title="Webinar: Modern Enterprise Java Architectures with Spring 3.1">Webinar: Modern Enterprise Java Architectures with Spring 3.1</a>
    </h2>
  
  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
          Submitted by Adam Fitzgerald on Thu, 2012-01-12 20:39        </div>
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"> in <ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_4 first last"><a href="/taxonomy/term/4" rel="tag" title="News and announcements
">News and Announcements</a></li>
</ul></div>
          </div>
  
  <div class="content">
    <p>In its 3.1 generation, the <a href="/spring-core">Spring Framework</a> presents itself as a versatile open source platform for Java-based application architectures on any kind of deployment platform. This webinar on January 19th covers the key feature set in <a href="http://www.springsource.com/download/community?project=Spring%20Framework&amp;version=3.1.0.RELEASE">Spring 3.1</a>, from environment profiles and Java-based application configuration to declarative caching and Servlet 3.0 support. Spring 3.1's capabilities will be discussed in the context of current trends such as cloud computing and HTML 5, influencing the way enterprise Java applications will be built in 2012 and beyond.</p>
<p>Join <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/author/juergenh/">Juergen Hoeller</a> and <a href="http://blog.springsource.org/author/cbeams/">Chris Beams</a> for this great opportunity to learn all about the recent Spring 3.1 release:</p>
<ul>
<li>Europe: <a href="https://vmwareevents.webex.com/vmwareevents/onstage/g.php?t=a&amp;d=663415641">January 19, 3:00pm UK / 4:00pm Europe</a></li>
<li>North America: <a href="https://vmwareevents.webex.com/vmwareevents/onstage/g.php?t=a&amp;d=668718779">January 19, 1:00pm EST / 10:00am PST</a></li>
</ul>
  </div>

  <ul class="links inline"><li class="comment_forbidden first last"></li>
</ul>
